quilibrium over the photospheric regions. Finally,\nwe find that our retrieved effective temperatures are lower than previous\ninferences for some objects and that our radii are larger than expectations\nfrom evolutionary models, possibly indicative of un-resolved binaries. This\ninvestigation and methodology represents a paradigm in linking spectra to the\ndetermination of the fundamental chemical and physical processes governing cool\nbrown dwarf atmospheres.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 8 Dec 2016 20:47:28 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 9 Dec 2016 01:46:16 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 25 Jul 2017 00:36:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-10-25"}
