}(r_{p})$ within an accuracy of 5% for $\\sigma_{z} = 0.001 \\times (1 +\nz_{c})$ and within 10% for $\\sigma_{z} = 0.03 \\times (1 + z_{c})$. The\nevolution of the correlation in redshift and mass is clearly detected for all\n$\\sigma_{z}$ tested. The best-fit parameters $(r_{0}$ and ${\\gamma})$ as well\nas the bias obtained from the deprojection method for all $\\sigma_{z}$ are\nwithin the $1 \\sigma$ uncertainty of the $z_{c}$ sample.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 8 Dec 2016 21:00:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 13 Jan 2017 16:19:34 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-03-29"}
